item.title: Sigmund Freud and Sensibility
item.description: This paper focuses on Chapter Two of Civilization and Its Discontents, where Freud introduces the pleasure and reality principles as mechanisms that govern human happiness and suffering.

item.title: Your Inner Hedgehog
item.description: This paper describes the inner hedgehog, a psychological condition widespread in academia. Published in the Journal of Socio-Experimental Psychology, 2021.

item.title: Where Are You Going, Where Have You Been? : Analytical Summary Essay
item.description: This is an analytical essay exploring Joyce Carol Oates’ use of symbolism in “Where Are You Going, Where Have You Been?”.
